Since the easing of COVID-19 restrictions, China's economy has seen rapid recovery and development, with foreign investments pouring into the Chinese financial market. The cumulative net inflow of funds has surpassed 150 billion yuan ($22 billion) since the start of 2023. International investors are increasingly confident in the country's robust economic recovery, as evidenced by their increasing holdings of Chinese assets. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zhu Zhu explains.